data.value:
Verse 1:
Too many people are tryin' to change me
Too many people are lookin' to rearrange me
But the last thing I'll ever do
To prove that I am a man like you

Verse 2
Is work from nine to five tryin' to keep myself alive
And have to listen every day to everybody's jive
And concentrate my time on simply tryin' to make a dime
And agitate my mind on tryin' to make our values rhyme

Chorus:
Too many things that I've got to do
Too many bags that I've got to run through
And the last thing I'll ever do
To prove that I am a man like you

Bridge:
Is turn away the girls even though I want a whirl
And worry just because that's what everybody else does
And chase myself around so that I'm not called a clown
Wear a suit and tie when I'd rather sit and die

Verse 1:
You want to relax,
All you gotta do is let me do everything,
Just let go of your tasks,
Don't worry, everything will be just fine.

Chorus:
Find yourself inside your mind
Don't be in panic, be relaxed.

Verse 2:
Find your peace, find your strength,
And when you reach your confidence,
Lying down, relaxing, and sensing the nature.

Bridge:
Find that you're not the kind to face the ugliness of reality,
Stay by the truth and we will find the calmness to stay in all its splendid beauty.
Verse 1:
Too many people trying to change me
Looking to attack me verbally
The last thing I'll ever do
Is to please narrow-minded people like you

Pre-Chorus:
You're too weak trying to please the masses
Looking to conform to the mainstream

Chorus:
Too many things that I got to beware
Social rules that I got to run through
The last thing I'll ever do
Is to prove that I am thinking like you

Verse 2:
Working from nine to five trying to keep myself alive
Listening everyday to what people want to talk about
Concentrating my time on just trying to make a dime
Agitating my mind on trying to make my mind to match the reality

Pre-Chorus:
You're too weak trying to please everyone
Looking to conform to stereotypes

Bridge:
Turning away the girls even though I want a wife
Worrying just because I feel incomplete
Doing what women want so that I'm not called a clown
Wearing a suit and tie when I'd rather sit and die
Verse 3:
City lights shining in the dark
Don't worry it's just life
Their trust have reached balance
You'll find you'll have a lovely time

parts.name: Verse 1
source: Too many people trying to change me
Looking to attack me verbally
The last thing I'll ever do
Is to please narrow-minded people like you
ai_source: People attempting to mold me to their boxed views
Seeking retaliation in furious retorts
The one thing I will never commit
Is to conform to their rigid preconceptions

source: Too many people trying to change me
Looking to attack me verbally

suggestion.content:
Friends they all come tryin' to change me,
Tryin' to tear me down, brazenly.

They all come at me, tryin' to change me,
Tryin' to belittle me, obscenely.

All these folks, they wanna change me,
Lookin' to shred me destructively.

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
Too many folks tryin' to change me,
Seekin' to stain me unwontedly.

Round here folks tryin' to change me,
Stressin' me out, relentlessly.

Tried to hide it, but they ain't changin' me,
Wanna cheapen me down, indiscreetly.

Many try to change me, make me see,
Gonna stay true to me, heedlessly.

Many folks think they can change me,
Hotly desire to control me.

People keep sayin', they can change me,
Never gonna lay down, warily.

Try to stop me but it ain't changin' me,
Revealin' my truth, dauntlessly.

Lookin' around, folks tryin' to change me,
Entitled their thoughts, brazenly.

New crowds tryin' to change me,
Tryin' take away my sanity.

So many folks comin' to change me,
Tryin' to break me fatally.

Mendacious folks tryin' to change me,
Swayed by temptation, sorrowfully.

Try to place me in their dominion,
Defy 'em, they can't change me.

Crowds all joke, tryin' to change me,
Virtue intact, proudly I'm free.

Too many faces tryin' to change me,
Steadfast I'm standin', faithfully.

People so cruel, tryin' to change me,
Fall from my throne, quickly I'm free.

source: The last thing I'll ever do
Is to please narrow-minded people like you

suggestion.content:
No more lies, I'm off to find my way,
A step closer to a brighter day.

An end to lies, confused and torn,
My spirit, freedom, shall be reborn.

Let the truth be bold and clear,
Reclaim my soul, loud and clear.

suggestion.style: Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five
suggestion.content:
No more lies, can't take no more,
My dreams, oh, they will soar.

Time to shed these chains I wear,
Living life with no more fear.

The truth I seek, shines from the sky,
Choice is mine, and I cannot deny.

Fresh start, I'm keen to begin,
Ain't no time like the present, amen.

Yesterday, I was imprisoned,
Declared my freedom, 'tis decided.

Lies been told, I can't sustain,
My life free of further pain.

Living life, no more confined,
Rising high, the clouds resigned.

Wouldn't let me live in vain,
Leaving here, destiny claim.

My path clear, I just can't lose,
Nothing gonna stand in my shoes.

No more games, no more pain,
Set off to freedom, I remain.

My path done, your word not true,
Lead my soul toward something new.

No more mask, it has to go,
Gravity of truth, I now know.

Death to cage, to which I'm bound,
Soaring high, my spirit found.

My old ways, no more depend,
Live anew, no need to pretend.

No more fear, I must be me,
Time to carve a destiny.

parts.name: Chorus
source: Too many things that I got to beware
Social rules that I got to run through
The last thing I'll ever do
Is to prove that I am thinking like you
ai_source: Too many troubles getting in my way
Navigating around societal dogma
The one thing I will never do
Is to bend my spirit to the whims of you

parts.name: Verse 2
source: Working from nine to five trying to keep myself alive
Listening everyday to what people want to talk about
Concentrating my time on just trying to make a dime
Agitating my mind on trying to make my mind to match the reality
ai_source: Days spent hustling just to stay afloat
Hearkening to their hollow empty talks
Shelling out hours to bring in a few coins
Imprisoning my talent to make a career in conformity

parts.name: Bridge
source: Turning away the girls even though I want a wife
Worrying just because I feel incomplete
Doing what women want so that I'm not called a clown
Wearing a suit and tie when I'd rather sit and die
ai_source: Showing myself for what it's really worth
Incomplete, unsatisfied, but seeking more
Meeting women halfway to turn my luck around
Swapping out my hoodies for power ties

parts.name: Pre-Chorus
source: You're too weak trying to please everyone
Looking to conform to stereotypes
ai_source: Cower not from their pressure commands
Bow not to their unreasonable demands

parts.name: Verse 3
source: City lights shining in the dark
Don't worry it's just life
Their trust have reached balance
You'll find you'll have a lovely time
ai_source: Soaring through the city night, plunging with delight
Forget the frustration, seize these precious moments of life.
Our trust has reached equilibrium
You'll create an enchanting experience
